<br>
Actually screen lag is more of a matter of DRAM. If you have a Voodoo card with 32mb that's actually good enough, so long as you dont pig out on max clipping planes. It's true that if you have less than a 32mb Voodoo/GeForce/NVidia card, then frame rates will be compromised. But as I've read many many times, your typical screen lag from places like Swamp of No Hope aka Texture Hell (very classic example here) is because the PC does not have enough RAM to process all the texture graphics.... what ends up happening is that the hard drive has to end up caching those textures momentarily.... and since HD speed is much slower than RAM speed, that's why players will realize the socalled lag. I've just seen many players say they had this problem, and then they went out and doubled their RAM.... and voila, the screenlag probs start to disappear. <br>
<br>
So when Verant says that SoL reeeeeeally &quot;recommends&quot; 512mb of RAM.... they aren't horsing around. They really mean it. Even 256mb is considered just &quot;minimum requirements&quot;.... which translates in English to &quot;you can run the darn thing, but don't expect to be happy about the performance&quot; <br>
<br>
I think that Verant made a miscalculation when they jumped to an expansion that recommends 512mb RAM to play smoothly. That kind of expectation simply caught a lot of players off guard. In fact very few top-of-the-line PC games today ever require that amount of RAM..... altho it might be the norm in the next 12-18 months. <br>
<br>
just my 2pp<br>
<br>
